IRS990.ActivityOrMissionDesc: TO CULTIVATE PARTNERSHIPS SUPPORTING AGRICULTURAL EDUCATION & PROVIDE FINANCIAL SUPPORT(SCH O)TO ASSIST AGRICULTURAL EDUCATION ORGANIZATIONS IN ACCOMPLISHING THEIR MISSIONS.
IRS990.MissionDesc: THE IOWA FFA FOUNDATION CULTIVATES PARTNERSHIPS SUPPORTING AGRICULTURAL EDUCATION AND ALSO SEEKS AND PROVIDES FINANCIAL SUPPORT TO ASSIST AGRICULTURAL EDUCATION ORGANIZATIONS IN ACCOMPLISIHING THEIR MISSIONS.
IRS990.Desc: THE FOUNDATION SUPPORTS THE DEVELOPMENT OF QUALITY AGRICULTURAL EDUCATION PROGRAMS FOR HIGH SCHOOL STUDENTS, FFA MEMBERS, FFA CHAPTERS, AND OTHERS THROUGH PROFICIENCY AWARDS, CAREER DEVELOPMENT EVENTS, EXHIBITOR AWARDS, SCHOLARSHIP PROGRAMS, INCENTIVE AWARDS, AGRICULTURAL EDUCATION INSTRUCTIONAL MATERIALS, SEMINARS, CONFERENCES, WORKSHOPS, AND OTHER ACTIVITIES.

Form990ScheduleAPartVIGrp.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: SCHEDULE A, PART II, LINE 10, EXPLANATION OF OTHER INCOME:

SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: BOARD-DESIGNATED FUNDS ARE AVAILABLE FOR BUILDING MAINTENANCE, OPERATIONS, AND SCHOLARSHIPS. INCOME FROM PERMANENTLY RESTRICTED FUNDS MUST BE USED FOR SCHOLARSHIPS.
RENTAL AND PERSONAL PROPERTY EXPENSE NETTED 637,355. FUNDRAISING EXPENSE NETTED 30,223.
RENTAL AND PERSONAL PROPERTY EXPENSE NETTED 637,355. FUNDRAISING EXPENSE NETTED 30,223.

FUNDS ARE PROVIDED TO THE IOWA FFA ASSOCIATION, IOWA AGRICULTURAL TEACHERS ACROSS IOWA, AND IOWA POSTSECONDARY AGRICULTURAL STUDENT ASSOCIATION FOR SPONSORSHIPS OF STUDENT AWARDS AND SCHOLARSHIPS BASED ON INDEPENDENTLY-JUDGED COMPETITIONS FOCUSING ON SPECIFIC AG-RELATED CAREER SKILLS. JUDGES ARE TYPICALLY INDEPENDENT ALUMNI OR INDEPENDENT REPRESENTATIVES OF BUSINESS AND INDUSTRY GROUPS. THE FFA FOUNDATION MONITORS THE USE OF THESE AWARDS BY VERIFYING THAT THE SELECTED RECIPIENTS RECEIVE THE AWARDS. SCHOLARSHIPS AND AWARDS ARE PRESENTED FOR A WIDE VARIETY OF AG-RELATED EXPERIENCES, CAREER GOALS, AND HIGHER EDUCATION PLANS. SCHOLARSHIP AND AWARD APPLICATIONS ARE REVIEWED BY AN INDEPENDENT COMMITTEE AND SELECTIONS ARE MADE BASED ON PREDETERMINED CRITERIA.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: FORM 990, PART VI, SECTION B, LINE 11B
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: MANAGEMENT AND THE FINANCE COMMITTEE ARE PROVIDED A DRAFT COPY OF THE COMPLETE RETURN BEFORE FILING. AFTER A DETAILED REVIEW, THE FULL BOARD RECEIVES A COPY OF THE COMPLETED RETURN FOR FINAL APPROVAL PRIOR TO FILING.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: FORM 990, PART VI, SECTION B, LINE 12C
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: DIRECTORS WOULD ARTICULATE POTENTIAL CONFLICTS TO FULL BOARD. BOARD OF DIRECTORS MONITORS AND ENFORCES COMPLIANCE WITH THE CONFLICT OF INTEREST POLICY.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: FORM 990, PART VI, SECTION B, LINE 15A
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: BOARD OF DIRECTORS (ALL OF WHOM ARE INDEPENDENT) IS RESPONSIBLE FOR COMPENSATION-RELATED MATTERS. BOARD APPROVES COMPENSATION OF EXECUTIVE DIRECTOR AND OTHER EMPLOYEES (ORGANIZATION HAS SEVEN FULL-TIME EMPLOYEES) AND CONTEMPORANEOUSLY SUBSTANTIATES DELIBERATION AND DECISION. ALTHOUGH FORMAL COMPARABILITY DATA IS NOT OBTAINED FOR COMPARISON TO COMPENSATION OF EXECUTIVE DIRECTOR OF THE FFA FOUNDATION, BOARD IS FAMILIAR WITH OTHER SIMILAR-SIZED AG-RELATED NONPROFIT EDUCATION ENTITIES AND BELIEVES EXECUTIVE DIRECTOR COMPENSATION IS REASONABLE. OTHER THAN EXECUTIVE DIRECTOR, THERE ARE NO OTHER TOP MANAGEMENT, COMPENSATED OFFICERS OR OTHER KEY EMPLOYEES.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: FORM 990, PART VI, SECTION C, LINE 19
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: DISCLOSURE OF GOVERNING DOCUMENTS, POLICIES AND FINANCIAL STATEMENTS IS PROVIDED UPON REQUEST.
